HEADWORD: Subconsciousness
<hw>Sub*con"scious*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state
or quality of being subconscious; a state of mind in which perception
and other mental processes occur without distinct
consciousness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

